observations.recommendation:
To fairly present the balances of the cash in bank and the corresponding payable/liability accounts at the end of the year, we recommended that Management:

a. Instruct the accounting personnel to prepare a JEV to take up the unclaimed checks in accordance with the above-cited provision;

b. Henceforth, observe the same every end of the year.

a. Stop the granting of additional cash advances to officials and employees with outstanding balances;

b. Stop granting cash advances other than travel expenses to an elective official of the Municipality;

c. Stop the practice of granting cash advances for expenses other that travel expenses to officials and employees of the Municipality who are not bonded and not designated as special disbursing officers;

d. Strictly enforce the liquidation and collection of the above stated unliquidated cash advances;

e. The Municipal Accountant shall demand for the liquidation of the above stated unliquidated cash advances;

f. In the subsequent granting of cash advances and in order to prevent the accumulation of unliquidated cash advances, the Municipal Accountant shall send within ten (10) days before the expiration of the 30 days period written notices/reminders and letters enjoining the officers and employees to liquidate their travel cash advances.

To fairly present the balances of the cash in bank and the corresponding payable/liability accounts at the end of the year, we recommended that Management:
a. Instruct the accounting personnel to prepare a JEV to take up the unclaimed checks in accordance with the above-cited provision;
b. Henceforth, observe the same every end of the year.

With the deficiencies discussed, we recommend for Management to:

a. Instruct the Municipal Accountant and Municipal Treasurer to ensure that funds transferred to LDRRMF includes not only 5% from the IRA but also from other local sources of income;

b. Require the MDRRMO to prepare the monthly Utilization Report duly reconciled with the accounting records and certified correct by the Municipal Accountant.

a. Stop the granting of additional cash advances to officials and employees with outstanding balances;

b. Stop granting cash advances other than travel expenses to an elective official of the Municipality;

c. Stop the practice of granting cash advances for expenses other that travel expenses to officials and employees of the Municipality who are not bonded and not designated as special disbursing officers;

d. Strictly enforce the liquidation and collection of the above stated unliquidated cash advances;

e. The Municipal Accountant shall demand for the liquidation of the above stated unliquidated cash advances;

f. In the subsequent granting of cash advances and in order to prevent the accumulation of unliquidated cash advances, the Municipal Accountant shall send within ten (10) days before the expiration of the 30 days period written notices/reminders and letters enjoining the officers and employees to liquidate their travel cash advances.

a. In the disbursement of government funds, the Municipality shall provide the necessary supporting documents as required under COA Circular No. 2012-001 and in compliance with Sections 4(6) and 7 of P.D. 1445;

b. Require the submission of liquidation of cash advances to the accounting office;

c. Direct the office of the MSWD to maintain proper monitoring and Storage of RGFPs.

a. Direct the concerned Accounting personnel to (i) stop immediately the remittance of Pag-IBIG Fund government share in excess of the prescribed rate; (ii) adhere strictly to the laws/regulations on the Pag-IBIG Fund Contributions (government share) as provided in Section 7 of RA 9679;

b. Instruct the Municipal Accountant to request Pag-IBIG Fund to consider the excess amount as advance payment of government share in future remittance, otherwise this shall be refunded by officials and employees concerned; and

c. Strengthen the internal control system particularly the review of remittances on statutory obligations to prevent from recurrence of the deficiency.
